The Governing Council of the Benson Idahosa University (BIU) has okayed the appointment of a professor of Fisheries, Johnson Oyedeji, as the Deputy Vice Chancellor (DVC). The Acting Head, Communications and Brand Strategy Unit (CBSU), Mr. Temi Esonamunjor, who made this known in a statement, said Oyedeji’s appointment was announced at the council’s 96th Regular Meeting. Until his appointment, Oyedeji was a former Dean of the Faculty of Agriculture and Agricultural Technology of the university. He has also held several administrative positions in the institution. He is a Fellow of the Fisheries Society of Nigeria (FISON) and Institute of Corporate Administration.